# Researcher — Client Finder 1.0 (Build-Prep)
slug: `client-finder-1-0` | role: researcher | phase: build-prep

---

## 1. Scaffold Commands (run from upwork-runs/client-finder-1-0/)

```bash
mkdir demo-src && cd demo-src
npm create vite@5 . -- --template react
# accept defaults, then:
npm install
npm install @huggingface/transformers@3
# exact versions locked below; no other runtime deps needed
```

---

## 2. Exact package.json

```json
{
  "name": "client-finder-1-0",
  "private": true,
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "vite",
    "build": "vite build",
    "preview": "vite preview"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@huggingface/transformers": "^3.0.0",
    "react": "^18.3.1",
    "react-dom": "^18.3.1"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@vitejs/plugin-react": "^4.3.4",
    "vite": "^5.4.11"
  }
}
```

**No other runtime deps.** CSV export = plain JS. No react-table, no charting lib — hand-rolled table keeps bundle tight and avoids ESM compat issues.

---

## 3. vite.config.js (exact)

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  base: '/demos/client-finder-1-0/',
  build: {
    outDir: '../../../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/client-finder-1-0',
    emptyOutDir: true,
  },
  optimizeDeps: {
    exclude: ['@huggingface/transformers'],
  },
  worker: {
    format: 'es',
  },
});
```

`optimizeDeps.exclude` is required — `@huggingface/transformers` v3 self-handles its own chunking and pre-bundling breaks the WASM/WebGPU shims.

