## 5. Screenshot Placeholder Strategy

- Create `public/demos/client-finder-1-0/assets/screenshots/` in the michaelwegter.com repo.
- Add one generic placeholder PNG: `placeholder.png` (dark gray gradient, ~400x300px, "No Screenshot" label in white monospace).
- In seedLeads.js use `screenshot_url: import.meta.env.BASE_URL + 'assets/screenshots/placeholder.png'` for all 50 leads.
- The WebGPUPanel "Analyze a Website" flow: capture a data URL from a canvas or use a seeded placeholder; POST the audit result back — no live screenshot fetch needed for the demo.

---

## 6. useWebGPU.js — Critical Patterns

```js
// hooks/useWebGPU.js
import { useState, useCallback } from 'react';

export function useWebGPU() {
  const [gpuInfo, setGpuInfo] = useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [progress, setProgress] = useState(0);
  const [progressMsg, setProgressMsg] = useState('');
  const [result, setResult] = useState(null);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);
  const [backend, setBackend] = useState(null); // 'webgpu' | 'wasm'

  const detectGPU = useCallback(async () => {
    if (!navigator.gpu) { setGpuInfo({ available: false }); setBackend('wasm'); return; }
    try {
      const adapter = await navigator.gpu.requestAdapter();
      const info = await adapter.requestAdapterInfo();
      setGpuInfo({ available: true, vendor: info.vendor, architecture: info.architecture, device: info.device, description: info.description });
      setBackend('webgpu');
    } catch (e) {
      setGpuInfo({ available: false, error: e.message }); setBackend('wasm');
    }
  }, []);

  const runAudit = useCallback(async (imageUrl) => {
    setLoading(true); setProgress(0); setProgressMsg('Initializing...'); setError(null);
    try {
      const { pipeline } = await import('@huggingface/transformers');
      const dev = backend === 'webgpu' ? 'webgpu' : 'wasm';
      setProgressMsg(`Loading SmolVLM-256M model (${dev.toUpperCase()})...`);
      const pipe = await pipeline(
        'image-text-to-text',
        'HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct',
        {
          device: dev,
          progress_callback: (p) => {
            if (p.status === 'downloading') {
              setProgress(Math.round((p.loaded / p.total) * 60));
              setProgressMsg(`Downloading model weights... ${Math.round((p.loaded / p.total) * 100)}%`);
            } else if (p.status === 'loading') {
              setProgress(75); setProgressMsg('Loading into GPU memory...');
            }
          },
        }
      );
      setProgress(85); setProgressMsg('Running vision analysis...');
      const prompt = `You are a web design auditor. Analyze this website screenshot and rate it 1-10 for:
1. UI Modernity (visual design, typography, layout)
2. Mobile Responsiveness (flexible layout, touch targets)
3. Overall Functionality (navigation clarity, content structure)
Respond in JSON: {"modernity":N,"mobile":N,"function":N,"notes":"2-3 sentences of specific observations","outdated_signs":["list"]}`;
      const out = await pipe([{ role: 'user', content: [{ type: 'image', image: imageUrl }, { type: 'text', text: prompt }] }]);
      setProgress(100); setProgressMsg('Complete');
      // Parse JSON from the generated text
      const text = out[0]?.generated_text ?? out[0]?.message?.content ?? '';
      const match = text.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
      if (match) setResult(JSON.parse(match[0]));
      else setResult({ raw: text });
    } catch (e) {
      setError(e.message);
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  }, [backend]);

  return { gpuInfo, backend, loading, progress, progressMsg, result, error, detectGPU, runAudit };
}
```

**Critical notes for demo-builder:**
- Import `pipeline` lazily (`await import(...)`) inside runAudit — do NOT top-level import. This avoids loading the 256MB model until the user clicks "Analyze".
- The progress_callback format changed in v3: check `p.status` not `p.file`.
- iframe WebGPU restriction: `navigator.gpu` is undefined inside a sandboxed iframe on some browsers. WebGPUPanel MUST detect this and show: `"WebGPU unavailable in iframe — <a href='/demos/client-finder-1-0/' target='_blank'>open demo directly</a> to enable GPU inference."` Use `window.self !== window.top` to detect iframe context.
- WASM fallback is auto-triggered by `device: 'wasm'` — same pipeline() call, just slower (~30-60s).

