## 8. seedLeads.js — Frontend Seed (localStorage/API fallback)

**Purpose:** Used by `useLeads.js` as the fallback when API is unavailable (local dev or iframe CORS). The frontend should attempt `GET /clientfinder/leads` first; if it fails (network error / 5xx), fall back to this array and operate in `localStorage` mode.

The content should mirror _SEED_LEADS above, serialized as a JS export. Demo-builder: generate this from the Python dict above by converting Python True/False to JS true/false and None to null. Key mapping is identical.

```js
// src/data/seedLeads.js
// Auto-mirrored from backend _SEED_LEADS — keep in sync.
export const SEED_LEADS = [
  // paste the 50 objects here with JS boolean/null syntax
  // (same fields as the Python dicts above, identical structure)
];
```

