## 9. Design System — Additional Demo-Builder Cues

### Fonts (Google Fonts link for index.html)
```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```

### CSS Token Additions (tokens.css — items not in the plan)
```css
/* Layout */
--cf-sidebar-w: 260px;
--cf-header-h: 56px;
--cf-radius-sm: 4px;
--cf-radius-md: 8px;
--cf-radius-lg: 12px;

/* Shadows (dark theme) */
--cf-shadow-sm: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
--cf-shadow-md: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
--cf-shadow-lg: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);

/* Transitions */
--cf-transition: 150ms ease;

/* Z-index stack */
--cf-z-modal:   1000;
--cf-z-drawer:  900;
--cf-z-tooltip: 800;
```

### Layout Architecture
- **App shell:** fixed top nav (56px) + full-height main content below. NO sidebar needed — CRM is the main view; Discovery + WebGPU are tabs/panels within it.
- **Three top-level tabs** in the nav: `CRM` (default) | `Discovery` (opens drawer) | `WebGPU Audit`.
- CRM table: sticky header row, scrollable body. `table-layout: fixed` with explicit column widths.

### Score Chip Component (reuse everywhere)
```jsx
// StatusBadge.jsx handles both status + score chips
// Score chips: background = low/mid/high var; text = white; border-radius: 4px; padding: 2px 6px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums
function ScoreChip({ score }) {
  const color = score >= 7 ? 'var(--cf-score-high)' : score >= 4 ? 'var(--cf-score-mid)' : 'var(--cf-score-low)';
  return <span style={{ background: color, color: '#fff', borderRadius: 4, padding: '2px 6px', fontSize: 12, fontWeight: 600 }}>{score.toFixed(1)}</span>;
}
```

